---
description: Component system and design consistency rules
globs: ["src/**/*.tsx"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Use a composable component system.

Rules:
- reusable primitives belong in shared UI/component folders
- feature-specific composites belong inside feature folders
- do not duplicate button, modal, badge, panel, tabs implementations
- prefer composition over inheritance-like patterns
- keep component APIs small and explicit
- avoid giant god-components

Component guidelines:
- visual primitives: Button, IconButton, Badge, Panel, Input, Tabs, SplitPane, Modal
- feature components: CommitPanel, BranchSidebar, HistoryGraphPanel, DiffInspector, AIReviewPanel
- container components may fetch data and coordinate state
- presentational components should remain focused and reusable where possible

Do not:
- embed heavy data-fetching logic deep inside leaf components
- create multiple similar primitives with slightly different names
- introduce styling conventions that conflict with the shared design system